# Cursor Rules — maestro (core)

This repository is `maestro`: a product-development workspace with an agent control plane.

Product code lives in registered `apps/`, `services/`, `packages/`, `infra/`, and `tests/` roots.
Official documents live in `docs/`; external references awaiting curation go under `inputs/`.

> See also: `maestro-source.mdc` (when editing `services/**` or `src/**`), `maestro-runtime.mdc` (when editing `.maestro/runtime/**`), `maestro-spec.mdc` (when editing `.maestro/engine/**`).

## Framework Maintenance Scope

This repo is the `maestro` product-development control plane. `NEED_ONBOARDING`, an empty
component registry, and seed project knowledge are
expected for framework-only maintenance and must not block those changes.

For changes confined to framework docs, rules, templates, workflow agents, commands, tool adapters, or helper scripts:

- classify `target_scope: framework`
- set `requires_onboarding: false`
- read only entrypoints and directly relevant framework files
- select direct, assisted, or governed execution
- add Spec-Driven Development, Eval-Driven AI Development, or Enterprise Agent Governance overlays
  when traceability, eval-driven AI, or governed autonomous operation is required
- create a run under `.maestro/work/runs/` when work needs pause/resume, multiple attempts, trace/eval
  evidence, or human approval

Require onboarding only when assisted/governed product work depends on missing component facts.

## Read First

- `AGENTS.md`
- `CLAUDE.md`
- `COMMAND.md`
- `.maestro/engine/workflow.md`
- `.maestro/runtime/workflow-state.yaml`

## Core workflow rules (always)

- Route every natural-language request through `/coord`.
- Classify `target_scope` before broad brain/service reads.
- Use signature-first context loading before broad source reads: memory index, project/component profile summaries, context hints, then specific evidence files.
- Use `.maestro/config/model-routing.yaml` for agent model profiles and `.maestro/runtime/agent-activity.yaml` for `/status` activity/ETA reporting.
- Switch models through `.maestro/config/model-routing.yaml.model_overrides`; do not edit agent files or remove stable profiles to switch models.
- Use `.maestro/config/response-ui.yaml` for markdown/text response structure.
- Use `python3 scripts/status-dashboard.py --mode <compact|concise|dashboard|models|json>` as a terminal status mirror when project slash commands are not exposed. Add `--write` to generate `.maestro/runtime/reports/status.md` and `.maestro/runtime/reports/status.html`.
- Use `python3 scripts/agent-activity.py` for adapter telemetry updates and `python3 scripts/architecture-health-check.py --strict` for optional deterministic drift checks.
- Direct work may omit persistent artifacts; assisted work requires task.yaml; governed work requires
  task-analysis.yaml.context_plan before implementation.
- A task describes intended work; a run records one execution attempt with checkpoints, traces, evals,
  approvals, and reports when needed.
- Risk-Based Workflow Routing is the default methodology router; specialized methodologies are overlays selected from
  `.maestro/methodology.yaml` and `docs/governance/methodologies/selection-matrix.md`.
- Do not jump directly to workflow agents or generated coders from raw user input.
- Specialist advisors live under `.claude/agents/specialists/<category>/` (19 advisor-only experts). Invoke them in-pipeline per `R-016` and `task-analysis.yaml.advisory_required`; they only write `.maestro/work/tasks/<task_id>/advisories/<id>.yaml`, never application code, never assign coders or mark gates, and are never a raw-user entrypoint.
- Cursor enforces source/secret/destructive gates via `.cursor/hooks/*` (parity with the Claude `scripts/hooks/*` guards; see `R-017`). Do not weaken or bypass these hooks; resolve the underlying rule instead.
- If a required fact is missing, mark `unknown`, cite the evidence gap, and ask through Coordinator. Do not fabricate.
- Claims of "done" must include evidence (file path, command output, or artifact).
- Do not fabricate exact ETA. Use `unknown` or clearly marked estimates when Cursor does not expose reliable metrics.

## Task Folder Contract

Task IDs use `TASK-YYYYMMDD-NNN-slug`.

All task artifacts stay in `.maestro/work/tasks/<task_id>/`.

Artifact baseline depends on execution mode:

- direct: none
- assisted: `task.yaml`, `progress.yaml`, `verification.yaml`
- governed: `task-input.md`, `task.yaml`, `task-updates.yaml`, `task-analysis.yaml`, then phase artifacts

Implementation/QC artifacts are created only by the matching workflow phase:

- `architecture-review.yaml`
- `implementation-plan.yaml`
- `service-assignments.yaml`
- `coder-results.yaml`
- `dev-verification.yaml`
- `qc-handoff.md`
- `qc-test-results.yaml`
- `qc-delivery-report.md`
- `bugs.yaml`
- `memory-updates.yaml`

The canonical Dev-to-QC handoff is `.maestro/work/tasks/<task_id>/qc-handoff.md`.

## Commands

Use `COMMAND.md` for the canonical command list. Start with `/coord` unless the user intentionally invokes a specific command.

## Anti-Guessing

If a required fact is missing, use `unknown`, state the evidence gap, and ask through Coordinator. Do not fabricate project facts.
